Coloration in alcohol. Similar to living specimens, but with background color dark brown (see
Fig. 1
). Sexual dimorphism. Adult males have a fleshy flap in the surface of first ray of pelvic fin (absent in females) and a conspicuous papilla in urogenital opening (absent in females).

Distribution. Known only from córrego Tamborete, a small tributary of rio Grande (upper rio Paraná basin), municipality of Capitólio, Minas Gerais State, Brazil (
Fig. 3
).
